  <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/blog/putting-user-centre-everything" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-inline clearfix"><div class="field-label">Comment:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>I can strongly relate to your user-centric principle.</p>
<p>The design agency I run planned the digital strategy for DHS&#039;s first MyGov office in Turbot Street, Brisbane - using customer journey mapping to locate devices and determine content strategy for each touchpoint - it was all aimed at putting ourselves in the shoes of the customer.<br />
We find this technique really useful in designing integrated customer experiences that combine the 3 customer states - in-line, on-line and<br />
en-route. </p>
<p>We are happy to report this type of design thinking also works well in shopping centres, retail stores and the hospitality industry.<br />
we have even tested it in a Digital Experience Lab in Melbourne.</p>
<p>Exciting times ahead for digital transformation thinkers!</p>
